.DT
query_philosophy_argument
$MUDNAME$ Creator Help
query_philosophy_argument

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
query_philosophy_argument -  This method returns the values for the specific argument in philosophy.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
mixed query_philosophy_argument(string name,
string argument)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^name%^RESET%^ - the name of the philosphy to get the arguments for
%^BOLD%^argument%^RESET%^ - the name of the argument to return
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
an array of the arguments values
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/handlers/philosophies.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method returns the values for the specific argument in
philosophy.   The returned array consists of three values, they
are ({ skill, something, something }).
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
query_philosphy_bonus(), query_philosphy_type(), query_philosphy_needed(), query_philosphy_effect(), add_philosphy_argument(), remove_philosphy_argument()

.EP

